{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The research focuses on industrial control processors, characterized by single-core, single-thread, and fixed main frequency.",
    "The feature vectors for model training include dynamic instructions like load, store, unconditional branch, conditional branch, and integer, as well as static indicators like lines of code and functions.",
    "Energy consumption is correlated with the average execution time.",
    "Experiments use Mälardalen University benchmarks.",
    "Results show that the L-M neural network predicts WCET with an error rate of 16.43% and energy consumption with an error rate of 10.63%, outperforming the least squares support vector machine (LS-SVM) method, which had error rates of 25.63% for WCET and 22.41% for energy consumption.Amalou et al. [88] introduce a hybrid WCET estimation technique named WE-HML in their study."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Results show that the L-M neural network predicts WCET with an error rate of 16.43% and energy consumption with an error rate of 10.63%, outperforming the least squares support vector machine (LS-SVM) method, which had error rates of 25.63% for WCET and 22.41% for energy consumption.Amalou et al. [88] introduce a hybrid WCET estimation technique named WE-HML in their study."
